ce\n|\nLove has turned many into poets; pain has turned many into artists; charity has turned many into pacifists, and anger has turned many into activists.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nŠausmīgi daudz taisnību. Nojukt var, ja nav savējās.\n\n- Imants Ziedonis, Epifānijas\n|\nLife is a Treasure Hunt and we all have the key to it. Unfortunately, many of us don’t unlock it, but take the key to our grave.\n\n- RVM\n|\nWhen we choose to stay down, we are in reality confusing wisdom with cowardice. When we choose to stand back up, we are using wisdom to overcome cowardice.\n\n- Craig\n|\nIf a craftsman wants to do good work, he must first sharpen his tools.\n\n- Confucius, The Analects\n|\nWhen I want to read a novel, I write one.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nYou can't have everything, I've often noticed it.\n\n- Samuel Beckett, Molloy\n|\nTo tell you the truth, I'm something of an atheist.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, The Last Continent\n|\nWith Cosmic Ordering it’s not only your wealth that grows, your mind does too!\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nScience [is] that wonderfully convenient personification of the opinions, at a certain date, of Professors X, Y, and Z....\n\n- Aldous Huxley, Brave New World Revisited\n|\nThe way our minds work is that one positive thing and one negative thing does not equal each other.Instead, one negative thing can drastically bring down 2 or 3 positive things.\n\n- Osayi Emokpae Lasisi, Billionaire Mindset (for MoneyMaking Mommies): How to make your Billions and build your legacy\n|\nLife doesn't make any sense, and we all pretend it does. Comedy's job is to point out that it doesn't make sense, and that it doesn't make much difference anyway.\n\n- Eric\n|\n[W]hen trying to understand the character of the modern mind, it is impossible to separate the effects of genes and the developmental environment.\n\n- Steven Mithen, The Prehistory of the Mind: The Cognitive Origins of Art, Religion and Science\n|\nIn the end, the end of a life only matters to friends, family, and other folks you used to know. For everyone else, it's just another end.\n\n- Gabrielle\n|\nAlma, para llegar al infinito,da un impulso más firme a tu vuelo;sufre más!... ¡sufre más!... Tiene tu gritoalas, para elevarte sobre el suelo...\n\n- Luisa Luisi, Poemas de la Inmovilidad y Canciones al Sol\n|\nYou need to understand, comprehend and believe, “There is a goal in my birth. I have a mission, and there is something that no one but I can do.\n\n- Sunday\n|\nChase after the truth like all hell and you’ll free yourself, even though you never touch its coat tails.\n\n- Clarence\n|\nBut the past cannot be changed, and we carry our choices with us, forward, into the unknown. We can only move on.\n\n- Libba Bray, The Sweet Far Thing\n|\nWith the same habit of mind, even if you live thousands of lives, all will be the same! Get a different habit of mind to get a different life!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nAsk yourself: what is it, that if I believed it down to my core, would change everything?\n\n- Kamal Ravikant, Live Your Truth\n|\nI wasn't born to cook or clean,but to read and write,if you don't like me the way I am,then go fly a kite.\n\n- Besa\n|\nThere are two ways to go to the gas chamber, free and not free.\n\n- Jean-Paul\n|\nPats cīnies, palīdz, domā, spried un sver,Pats esi kungs, pats laimei – durvis ver!\n\n- Rainis\n|\nFirst visualize your goal in your mind. Then have a leap of faith, and let your passion guide you throughout the process.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, In Search of Divinity: Journey to The Kingdom of Conscience\n|\nThe question is not what you look at, but what you see.\n\n- Henry\n|\ncleave not to faith when faith brings blood.' - Rev. John Hale\n\n- Arthur Miller, The Crucible\n|\nSuccess is not how high you have climbed, but how you make a positive difference to the world.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nWhat else is a child, but hope? Hope for the future, hope for one's own salvation, hope for a tomorrow that shines as bright and warm as the best yesterday you can remember.\n\n- Emily Littlejohn, Inherit the Bones\n|\nTime is passing : not leaden steppingBut sprinting on winged feet,Quick silver slipping by.\n\n- Richard\n|\nIf you lived a good life, you either lived to save or died to save… that which must be saved and kept. Your life would never be meaningless. Not even for a moment.\n\n- Melita Tessy, Battle of the Spheres: Crust, Mantle and Core\n|\nLife is like soil – it will always return a harvest. If you plant good seeds, you’ll reap a bountiful harvest.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nThe most durable thing in writing is style, and style is the single most valuable investment a writer can make with his time.\n\n- Raymond\n|\nUnderstand that all motivation is internal, or intrinsic.\n\n- Del Suggs, Truly Leading: Lessons in Leadership\n|\nI suppose sooner or later in the life of everyone comes a moment of trial. We all of us have our particular devil who rides us and torments us, and we must give battle in the end.\n\n- Daphne du Maurier, Rebecca\n|\nIt was no mere accident you were sent to me, perfect synchronicity. Familiar souls wrapped in skin, brought together through time again.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nThe heaven of a grasshopper is the wheat field; the heaven of man is the same place, the very earth itself where we get our food and build our happiness!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nIf you could realize that everything is made out of time, then you can convert your free time into anything you want.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nLife's like a movie, write your own ending. Keep believing, keep pretending.\n\n- Jim\n|\nPunk rock should mean freedom, liking and excepting anything that you like. Playing whatever you want. As sloppy as you want. As long as it's good and it has passion.\n\n- Kurt\n|\nNot even waste/is inviolate./The day misspent,/the love misplaced,/has inside it/the seed of redemption./Nothing is exempt from resurrection.\n\n- Kay\n|\nBelieve in your heart that you're meant to live a life full of passion, purpose, magic and miracles.\n\n- Roy\n|\nIf your idea is not against your conscience or the will of God, go for it\n\n- Sunday\n|\nToday’s happiness depends on yesterday’s choice, just as today’s choice will determine tomorrow’s happiness.\n\n- RVM\n|\nThe truths of the one subject have already been discovered, but have not been accepted because they spell the death of the faith in the lie.\n\n- Compton\n|\nWithin our emotions lie answers, truths and instructions.\n\n- Sam Owen, 500 Relationships And Life Quotes: Bite-Sized Advice For Busy People\n|\nFor now, poetry has the capacity - in its own ways and by its own means - to remind us of something we are forbidden to see.\n\n- Adrienne\n|\nTo throw away an honest friend is, as it were, to throw your life away\n\n- Sophocles, Oedipus Rex\n|\nAh, happiness courts the light so we deem the world is gay. But misery hides aloof so we deem that misery there is none.\n\n- Herman Melville, Bartleby the Scrivener\n|\nThe fact that life has no meaning is a reason to live-moreover, the only one.\n\n- Emil\n|\nAs humans, we should be able to answer the question: “What do you do with your time?\n\n- Sunday\n|\nQuality, it seems, is a necessary, but insufficient attribute for success.\n\n- Derek Thompson, Hit Makers: Why Things Become Popular\n|\nMy most important piece of advice to all you would-be writers: When you write, try to leave out all the parts readers skip.\n\n- Elmore Leonard, Elmore Leonard's 10 Rules of Writing\n|\nAsking a working writer what he thinks about critics is like asking a lamp-post what it feels about dogs.', October 31, 1977]\n\n- John\n|\nWe will be remembered not by how much money we have left in the bank or by how many buildings and cars we owned, but by how many Lives we have touched and Transformed!\n\n- RVM\n|\nEverybody has to die. Why cry, when you have wings to fly!\n\n- RVM\n|\nYou have to master the art of selectivity in everything you do. Otherwise, you could be side-tracked by secondary events and opportunities.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nI ask, ‘Is the cup half-empty or half-full?’ And when I ask that question, I am amazed at how many people have no cup.\n\n- Craig\n|\nIt is difficult, when faced with a situation you cannot control, to admit you can do nothing.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, Horseradish\n|\nThis idea of perpetual happiness is crazy and overrated, because those dark moments fuel you for the next bright moments; each one helps you appreciate the other.\n\n- Brad\n|\nLive all you can: it's a mistake not to. It doesn't matter what you do in particular, so long as you have had your life. If you haven't had that, what have you had?\n\n- Henry James, The Ambassadors\n|\nTime is a great teacher, but Cosmic Ordering is a great provider.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nLove of love written by the broken hearted, love of life written by the dead.\n\n- Mark Z. Danielewski, House of Leaves\n|\nWenn man noch nicht das Leben kennt, wie sollte man den Tod kennen.\n\n- Confucius, Gespräche\n|\nScience is a tool of Common Sense. When we insist that all valid information come from science or doctors, Common Sense becomes uncommon or lost forever.\n\n- Richard\n|\nYou know, happiness isn't a permanent state. Neither is unhappiness. There's a flow, back and forth\n\n- Carole Glickfeld, Swimming Toward the Ocean: A Novel\n|\nAfter you have made the discovery of your own significance, you would then be able to find the reason to stay alive.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nTo my fellow authors heed these words with much importance, ' It is redundant for a true writer to sell their soul for literary fame, since the soul is a writer's inner voice...\n\n- Marcus\n|\nWe do not need to eat animals, wear animals, or use animals for entertainment purposes, and our only defense of these uses is our pleasure, amusement, and convenience.\n\n- Gary\n|\nHow absurd men are! They never use the liberties they have, they demand those they do not have. They have freedom of thought, they demand freedom of speech.\n\n- Søren\n|\nАко животните имаха разум, те също биха вършили глупости като хората.\n\n- Чудомир\n|\nPassion makes you good, but pride stops you to get better.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nLies run sprints, but the truth runs marathons.\n\n- Michael\n|\nWe are FREE, not bound like a Tree. We can Move, we can Dance... We can take a Chance!-RVM\n\n- RVM\n|\nNo one is absolutely free from religion and philosophy, for the life we live is always under the influence of religion and philosophy!\n\n- Ernest Agyemang Yeboah, Religion, Philosophy and life\n|\nThat you were able to walk away, gives me my answer as plain as day.\n\n- Alfa H, Abandoned Breaths\n|\nBlack and white is salt and pepper of colors, for life tastes bland without them.\n\n- Vikrmn, Corpkshetra\n|\nLove is happiness, but only when you believe it will last forever. Even though every time it turns out to be a lie, it’s only faith that gives love its strength and its joy.\n\n- Sergei Lukyanenko, Night Watch\n|\nIf you can't see a benefit of the challenges in the present, know that you're giving a present to your future.' —Bright Side Up: 100 Ways to Be Happier Right Now\n\n- Amy\n|\nThey say that just before you die your whole life flashes before your eyes, but that's not how it happened for me.\n\n- Lauren Oliver, Before I Fall\n|\nGet out of your own way… stop the paralysis by analysis… decide what you want, create a simple plan, and get moving!\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nMen love to wonder, and that is the seed of science.\n\n- Ralph\n|\nIt's harder to pick and choose when you're dead. It's like a photograph, you know. It doesn't matter as much.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, American Gods\n|\nLife is a bitter sweet journey my friend, a bitter sweet journey.\n\n- Luellen\n|\nLove, as life, is a journey. Finding true love for the ever after is an amazing achievement.\n\n- Fadi\n|\nAnd because Eddie knew that was only the truth, he said nothing.\n\n- Stephen King, The Waste Lands\n|\nPushing magic toward the candle, I willed it to light. Nothing happened.Irys made a strangled sound and the candle burned. “Are you directing your magic to the candle?”“Yes. W\n\n- Maria V. Snyder, Magic Study"